Package com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.graphs.gis

Interface Geo<V extends GeoPoint,E>

Type Parameters:
V - the vertex type, which must extend GeoPoint. Represents points in the graph.
E - the edge attribute type, representing properties of the connections between vertices.
All Superinterfaces:
EdgeGraph<V,E>, Graph<V,Edge<V,E>>
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseGeoGraph, GeoGraphSpherical
public interface Geo<V extends GeoPoint,E> extends EdgeGraph<V,E>
An interface defining the behavior of a geographic graph (Geo), where vertices represent geographic points, and edges represent relationships between these points, both with specific attributes. This interface extends the EdgeGraph interface, which models a graph structure with edges as primary entities.
